## Motorik and Krautrock Musical Structure\
\
The motorik beat is a 4/4 beat often used by drummers associated with krautrock, characterized by a kick drum-heavy, pulsating groove that created a forward-flowing feel. Krautrock structure typically removes the Verse Chorus Verse phrasing usually found in standard Rock genres and replaces it with the continuous driving, pulsating movement.\
\
Moving away from the patterns of song structure and melody of much rock music in America and Britain, some in the krautrock movement were drawn to a more mechanical and electronic sound.\
\
## Key Musical Elements\
\
Key elements of the classic Krautrock sound include the famed Motorik beat pioneered by Can's Jaki Liebezeit and Neu!'s Klaus Dinger, relying on a hypnotically regular four four pulse; a love of repetition and drone; extended improvisation; the use of synthesisers; and the influence of psychedelic music and avant-garde techniques.\
\
## Influence and Legacy\
\
The period contributed to the development of ambient music and techno, and influenced subsequent genres such as post-punk, new-age music, and post-rock.\
