\
## Key Figures and Origins\
\
The motorik beat was pioneered by Jaki Liebezeit, drummer with German experimental rock band Can, with Klaus Dinger of Neu!, another early pioneer of motorik, later calling it the "Apache beat".\
\
## The Motorik Rhythm Characteristics\
\
The Motorik beat is in 4/4 time signature and features three hits of a bass drum followed by one hit of a snare, working as a perfect loop for musicians to play over, evoking the feeling of motoring forward.\
\
Rother and Dinger, drawing directly from Liebezeit's innovations, honed motorik into a signature element of their minimalist rock, prioritizing steady eighth-note pulses on hi-hat and bass drum to evoke mechanical precision and endless propulsion.\
\
## Connection Between Artists\
\
Both Dinger and Neu! collaborator Michael Rother had been part of Kraftwerk's original line-up and left to work on a sound that was more organic than Kraftwerk's electronic directions.\
\
