What Real Motorik Intros/Outros Actually Do\
The canonical Neu!/Harmonia approach is not a build-up at all. It's a fade-in \'97 Conny Plank literally rode a fader between two tape machines. The full groove (drums + rhythm guitar) is already playing at bar 1; the listener just enters it mid-stream. The music pre-exists the listener's arrival. This is why Hallogallo feels so connected \'97 there is no "before the groove."\
\
Can's approach is different \'97 cold launch of the full groove at bar 1, all instruments together, immediately.\
\
What makes the current Zudio intros feel disconnected:\
\
Bass plays root-only (a single note held half a bar) \'97 completely unlike the actual bass pattern that defines the song\
Drums strip down to kick-only then gradually build \'97 this is a rock/post-punk convention, not a Motorik one\
The listener hears a simplified "different" song for 2-4 bars before the real song begins\
What real Motorik does instead:\
\
Play the actual patterns from bar 1, just at lower velocity \'97 the fade-in effect translated to MIDI\
Harmonic consistency throughout (same chord/center, already correct in Zudio)\
No tempo fluctuation \'97 the groove is metronomic from first note to last\
For outros:\
\
Neu!: fade-out \'97 same groove, velocity drops to silence\
Can/Cluster: last element playing is pads/keyboard texture, not drums\
Nobody does a hard cut (except maybe a joke outro like Broadcast's "Popcorn" parody)\
Proposed Changes\
Two weighted intro types, chosen randomly per song:\
\
Type A \'97 "Already Playing" (50%, Neu! style): Play the actual bass pattern + drums at ~55% velocity, ramping to full by the last bar. Pads at very low velocity from bar 1. No stripping of instruments \'97 just a velocity envelope across bars.\
\
Type B \'97 "Progressive Entry" (50%, Can style): Drums full pattern from bar 1 (not kick-only), bass plays a simplified but related version of its main pattern (root + fifth, not just root), pads enter on the last intro bar.\
\
For outros, two types:\
\
Type A \'97 "Fade" (50%): Full groove velocity ramps down across all outro bars.\
\
Type B \'97 "Dissolve to Pads" (50%): Drums fade over first half, bass fades bar 2-3, pads/texture hold through the final bar.\
\
